{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀστράπτω</b> <br /> (compare στράπτω), <i>Epic dialect</i> <i>imperfect</i> ἀστράπτεσκον[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus 2.86\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]: <i>future</i> ἀστράψω[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 53, 4th-5th c.AD(?): Nonnus Epicus “Dionysiaca” 33.376\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>aorist</i> ἤστραψα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 17.595, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>lighten, hurl lightnings,</b> frequently of omens sent by Zeus, ἀστράπτων ἐπιδέξι᾽[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 2.353; Κρονίδης ἐνδέξια σήματα φαίνων ἀστράπτει 9.237; ὡς δ᾽ ὅτ᾽ ἂν ἀστράπτῃ πόσις Ἥρης 10.5; ἀστράψας δὲ μάλα μεγάλ᾽ ἔκτυπε 17.595; οὑλύμπιος ἤστραπτεν, ἐβρόντα 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 531, compare “V.” 626. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>impersonal</i>, ἀστράπτει <b>it lightens,</b> ἤστραψε <b>it lightened,</b> οὐρανοῦ δ᾽ ἄπο ἤστραψε[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 578, compare 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Rhetorica” 1392b27. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>flash</b> or <b>glance like lightning,</b> πᾶς γὰρ ἀστράπτει χαλινός[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1067 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κατάχαλκον ἀ. πεδίον <b>gleams</b> with brass, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ph.” III; so ἀ. χαλκῷ 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 6.4.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the face, εἶδον τὴν ὄψιν.. ἀστράπτουσαν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedrus” 254b; ἀ. τοῖς ὄμμασι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Cynegeticus” 6.15 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of flowers, ἀνεμωνίδες ἀστράπτουσαι <b>bright,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Nicander Epicus “fragment” 74.64: with _accusative_ _cognate_, ἐξ ὀμμάτων δ᾽ ἤστραπτε.. σέλας (i.e. Τυφών)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>] <b>flashed</b> flame from his eyes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 358; ἵμερον ἀστράπτουσα κατ᾽ ὄμματος “Anthologia Graeca” 12.161 (3rd c.BC: Asclepiades Epigrammaticus), compare 2nd c.BC: Moschus Bucolicus [same place]; ἤστραψε γλυκὺ κάλλος “Anthologia Graeca” 12.110 (1st c.BC: Meleager Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> of persons, <b>to be brilliant, conspicuous,</b> ἔν τινι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.AD: Oppianus Apamensis Epicus “Cynegetica” 1.361, 2.23. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>transitive</i>, <b>consume with lightning,</b> uncertain in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Cratinus Comicus 53. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__III.2</b></Level3> <b>illuminate,</b> τι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.AD: Musaeus Epicus 276.\">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0797","accentedUnicode":"ἀστράπτω","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0792","matchingForm":"ἀστήρ","stepTransliteration":"astēr","gloss":"star","_zh_tw_Gloss":"星","_es_Gloss":"estrella","_zh_Gloss":"星"},{"strongNumber":"G0796","matchingForm":"ἀστραπή","stepTransliteration":"astrapē","gloss":"lightning","_zh_tw_Gloss":"閃電","_es_Gloss":"relámpago","_zh_Gloss":"闪电"},{"strongNumber":"G1823","matchingForm":"ἐξαστράπτω","stepTransliteration":"exastraptō","gloss":"to flash forth","_zh_tw_Gloss":"放光","_es_Gloss":"resplandecer ","_zh_Gloss":"放光"},{"strongNumber":"G4015","matchingForm":"περιαστράπτω","stepTransliteration":"periastraptō","gloss":"to shine","_zh_tw_Gloss":"照著, 四面照著","_es_Gloss":"brillar","_zh_Gloss":"照着, 四面照着"}],"shortDef":"to flash, gleam like lightning","mediumDef":"to flash, gleam like lightning <br /><b>to lighten, flash as lig